#This is a notebook on how to plot geo data and query and map different things.

first cell plots map of roads in ada ok.

library(osmdata)
## Data (c) OpenStreetMap contributors, ODbL 1.0. https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright
q <- opq(bbox = 'ada ok usa')
cway_sev <- osmdata_sp(q)
sp::plot(cway_sev$osm_lines)

the next cell we plot all the cinemas in ada ok.

if(!require("osmdata")) install.packages("osmdata")

library(tidyverse)
library(osmdata)
library(sf)
library(ggmap)


q <- opq(bbox = 'ada ok usa') %>%
     add_osm_feature("amenity", "cinema")
cinema <- osmdata_sf(q)

ada_map <- get_map(getbb("ada ok usa"), maptype = "toner-background")
## maptype = "toner-background" is only available with source = "stamen".
## resetting to source = "stamen"...
## Source : http://tile.stamen.com/terrain/12/947/1624.png
## Source : http://tile.stamen.com/terrain/12/948/1624.png
## Source : http://tile.stamen.com/terrain/12/949/1624.png
## Source : http://tile.stamen.com/terrain/12/947/1625.png
## Source : http://tile.stamen.com/terrain/12/948/1625.png
## Source : http://tile.stamen.com/terrain/12/949/1625.png
## Source : http://tile.stamen.com/terrain/12/947/1626.png
## Source : http://tile.stamen.com/terrain/12/948/1626.png
## Source : http://tile.stamen.com/terrain/12/949/1626.png
## Source : http://tile.stamen.com/terrain/12/947/1627.png

ggmap(ada_map)+
  geom_sf(data = cinema$osm_points,
          inherit.aes = FALSE,
          colour = "#238443",
          fill = "#004529",
          alpha = .5,
          size = 4,
          shape = 21)+
  labs(x = "", y = "")

the next cell plots all the supermarkets in ada ok

library(tidyverse)
q <- opq(bbox = 'ada ok usa') %>%
     add_osm_feature("shop", "supermarket")
ada_map <- get_map(getbb("ada ok usa"), maptype = "toner-background")
## maptype = "toner-background" is only available with source = "stamen".
## resetting to source = "stamen"...
ada_supermarkets <- osmdata_sf(q)
ggmap(ada_map)+
geom_sf(data = ada_supermarkets$osm_points,
          inherit.aes = FALSE,
          colour = "#238443",
          fill = "#004529",
          alpha = .5,
          size = 4,
          shape = 21)+
  labs(x = "", y = "")
## Coordinate system already present. Adding new coordinate system, which will replace the existing one.
